23/03/2003
BELGRADE, Serbia-Montenegro -- The Association of Serbian Judges vowed full support Friday (21 March) for the radical measures taken by the Serbian government to fight organised crime in the wake of Zoran Djindjic's assassination. 
Justice Minister Vladan Batic has said police are interrogating judges and prosecutors with suspected ties to the underworld.
On Saturday, the OSCE mission in Belgrade described organised crime as a major threat to the stability of the federation and the Balkan region. 
Various local and foreign institutions discussed the problem at a two-day, NATO-organised conference in Belgrade, which ended Saturday. 
Participants also talked about corruption and the shadow economy. 
(Tanjug, B92 - 22/03/03; Tanjug - 21/03/03)
